One base outfit ‚Üí three completely different looks. White tee + denim is one of the most reliable outfit bases you can have, because every layer you add changes the entire vibe. Here‚Äôs how to style it three ways: LOOK ONE: white tee + oxford shirt + structured bag ‚§∑ Rolling the sleeves and leaving the shirt open creates movement and keeps the outfit relaxed while still feeling intentional This is my go-to for everyday errands. Also, oxford shirts tend to be thicker than regular button ups which make them the perfect staple for fall! LOOK TWO: white tee + oxford + cable knit sweater over the shoulders ‚§∑ The sweater layer shifts the outfit into a more polished and elevated space instantly. It adds texture, contrast, and shape without feeling too heavy‚Äîa perfect fall transition trick! üòå LOOK THREE: white tee + oxford + v-neck sweater + tie ‚§∑ Using a crewneck sweater for this outfit might feel too suffocating or restricting. A v-neck sweater, on the other hand, will give you more space in the neckline for the tie to peek out of the collar. The reason why I like American Ivy/New England Prep style so much is because it uses layering to create visual interest as well as refinement while still staying comfortable.
